{
  "analysis": "The global configuration file `/usr/local/etc/pkg.conf` exists and contains package versions. Notably, it begins with a UTF-8 BOM (`\xEF\xBB\xBF`). The user override file `~/.pkg_override` does not exist, so the global configuration will be used. The next step is to extract the package versions (httpx==0.24.1 and requests==2.30.0) while handling the BOM and any whitespace issues.",
  "plan": "1. Use a combination of `sed` and `awk` to remove the BOM and any inconsistent whitespace around the equals sign in the global config file. 2. Extract the version strings for httpx and requests. 3. Store the cleaned version strings in shell variables for subsequent package installation.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "export HTTPX_VER=$(sed -e '1s/^\xef\xbb\xbf//' -e 's/^[ \t]*//' -e 's/[ \t]*$//' /usr/local/etc/pkg.conf | awk -F= '$1 == \"httpx\" {print $2}')\n",
      "duration": 0.1
